==English==

===Etymology===
From Middle English ''[[drinken#Middle English|drinken]]'', from Old English ''[[drincan]]''. Confer Dutch ''[[drinken#Dutch|drinken]]'', German ''[[trinken]]'', Old Norse ''[[drekka]]'', Gothic ''[[drigkan]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*drĭngk, /drɪŋk/, /drINk/

===Verb===
{{irregverb|'''to drink'''|'''[[drinks]]'''|'''[[drank]]'''|'''[[drunk]]'''|'''[[drinking]]'''}}

# To [[consume]] a [[liquid]] through the [[mouth]].
#:''You can lead a horse to water but you can't make him '''drink'''.''
# To [[consume]] [[alcoholic]] [[beverage]]s.
#: ''No thanks, I don't '''drink'''.''

